<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1914-01-21T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1914-01-21T00:00:00-05:00" n="1302" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d1302">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 312.115/47.</note>
                        <head>
                            <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to
                                chargé <persName type="to">O’Shaughnessy</persName>.</hi>
                        </head>
                        <opener>
                            <seg rendition="#center">[Telegram.]</seg>
                        </opener>
                        <opener>
                            <dateline rendition="#right">
                                <placeName>
                                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Department of State</hi>, <lb/>
                                    <hi rend="italic">Washington</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1914-01-21">
                                    <hi rend="italic">January 21, 1914</hi></date>.</dateline>
                        </opener>
                        <p>618. Your January 20. Instruct Consul at Progreso to enter formal protest
                            against attempt to impose forced loan upon American citizens but that if
                            authorities persist in attempt, to advise American citizens to pay under
                            protest making protest a matter of record if possible and to take
                            receipts.</p>
                        <closer>
                            <signed>
                                <hi rend="smallcaps">Bryan</hi></signed>.</closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>